mboxgrep
------------------------------------------
mboxgrep is a small utility that scans a mailbox for messages matching a
regular expression. Found messages can be either displayed on standard output,
counted, deleted, piped to a shell command or written to another mailbox.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.7-1
  libbz2_1-1.0.8-1
  libpcre2_32_0-10.45-1
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libbz2-devel-1.0.8-1
  libpcre-devel-8.45-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://mboxgrep.org/

Canonical download:
  https://git.datatipp.se/dspiljar/mboxgrep/archive/0.7.13.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mboxgrep-0.7.13-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mboxgrep-0.7.13-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mboxgrep-0.7.13-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mboxgrep-0.7.13-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mboxgrep)
  /usr/bin/mboxgrep.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mboxgrep.README
  /usr/share/doc/mboxgrep/AUTHORS.md
  /usr/share/doc/mboxgrep/COPYING.md
  /usr/share/doc/mboxgrep/NEWS.md
  /usr/share/doc/mboxgrep/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/mboxgrep/TODO.md
  /usr/share/info/mboxgrep.info.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/mboxgrep.1.gz

